## 4. END-TO-END (E2E) TESTING

### Standard: Playwright with critical path focus and real browser testing

**Critical Paths to Test:**
```
1. Authentication
   ├── Login with valid credentials
   ├── Login with invalid credentials
   ├── Logout
   ├── Session timeout
   └── Password reset

2. Client Management
   ├── Create client
   ├── Edit client
   ├── Delete client
   ├── Search client
   ├── CSV import
   └── Validate CUIT

3. Invoicing (Most Critical)
   ├── Create invoice
   ├── Select client (auto-fill)
   ├── Add line items
   ├── Calculate totals
   ├── Apply taxes (IVA)
   ├── Save invoice
   ├── Print invoice
   ├── Cancel invoice
   └── Verify audit trail

4. Permissions (RBAC)
   ├── User A cannot see User B data
   ├── Admin can approve invoices
   ├── Sales cannot access admin functions
   └── Tenant A data isolated from Tenant B

5. Error Handling
   ├── Network timeout
   ├── Server error (500)
   ├── Validation error (400)
   ├── Not found error (404)
   └── Unauthorized error (401)
```

**E2E Test Example:**
```typescript
// tests/e2e/critical-paths.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test'

test.describe('Critical User Paths', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    // Navigate to login page
    await page.goto('/login')
  })

  test('Login → Create Client → Create Invoice', async ({ page }) => {
    // Step 1: Login
    await page.fill('input[name="email"]', 'user@test.com')
    await page.fill('input[name="password"]', 'password123')
    await page.click('button[type="submit"]')
    
    // Verify redirect
    await expect(page).toHaveURL('/dashboard')

    // Step 2: Navigate to clients
    await page.click('text=Clientes')

    // Step 3: Create new client
    await page.click('button:has-text("Nuevo Cliente")')
    await page.fill('input[name="nombre"]', 'Test Client')
    await page.fill('input[name="cuit"]', '20123456789')
    await page.click('button:has-text("Guardar")')

    // Verify client created
    await expect(page.locator('text=Test Client')).toBeVisible()

    // Step 4: Navigate to invoicing
    await page.click('text=Facturación')
    await page.click('button:has-text("Nueva Factura")')

    // Step 5: Select client
    await page.fill('input[placeholder="Buscar cliente"]', 'Test Client')
    await page.click('text=Test Client')

    // Step 6: Add line item
    await page.click('button:has-text("Agregar Línea")')
    await page.fill('input[placeholder="Producto"]', 'Test Product')
    await page.fill('input[placeholder="Cantidad"]', '2')
    await page.fill('input[placeholder="Precio"]', '100')

    // Step 7: Verify calculation (2 × 100 = 200, + 20% IVA = 240)
    const total = await page.locator('text=/Total.*240/').textContent()
    expect(total).toBeDefined()

    // Step 8: Save invoice
    await page.click('button:has-text("Guardar")')

    // Verify success
    await expect(page.locator('text=Factura creada')).toBeVisible()
  })

  test('RBAC: Regular user cannot access admin panel', async ({ page }) => {
    // Login as regular user
    await page.fill('input[name="email"]', 'user@test.com')
    await page.fill('input[name="password"]', 'password123')
    await page.click('button[type="submit"]')

    // Try to access admin panel
    await page.goto('/admin')

    // Verify access denied
    expect(page.url()).not.toContain('/admin')
    await expect(page.locator('text=Access Denied')).toBeVisible()
  })

  test('Error handling: Validation error shows message', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.fill('input[name="email"]', 'user@test.com')
    await page.fill('input[name="password"]', 'password123')
    await page.click('button[type="submit"]')

    // Create client with invalid CUIT
    await page.click('text=Clientes')
    await page.click('button:has-text("Nuevo Cliente")')
    await page.fill('input[name="nombre"]', 'Test')
    await page.fill('input[name="cuit"]', 'INVALID')
    await page.click('button:has-text("Guardar")')

    // Verify error message
    await expect(page.locator('text=CUIT inválido')).toBeVisible()
  })
})
```

**Best Practices:**
- ✅ Test complete user workflows (not just individual screens)
- ✅ Use realistic test data
- ✅ Wait for elements explicitly (no arbitrary sleeps)
- ✅ Test across browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari)
- ✅ Verify both UI and API state
- ✅ Test error scenarios
- ✅ Test RBAC and multi-tenant isolation
- ❌ Don't test third-party components
- ❌ Don't use hardcoded delays (use waitFor)
- ❌ Don't test CSS (visual regression for that)

