## 7. VISUAL REGRESSION TESTING

### Standard: Automated screenshot comparison with baseline management

**Playwright Snapshots:**
```typescript
// tests/visual/visual-regression.spec.ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test'

test.describe('Visual Regression Tests', () => {
  test('login page matches baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/login')
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle')
    expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('login-page.png')
  })

  test('form inputs match baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/clientes/nuevo')
    expect(await page.locator('form').screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('cliente-form.png')
  })

  test('table layout matches baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('/facturas')
    await page.waitForLoadState('networkidle')
    expect(await page.locator('table').screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('invoice-table.png')
  })

  test('responsive design: mobile view', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.setViewportSize({ width: 375, height: 667 })
    await page.goto('/dashboard')
    expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('dashboard-mobile.png')
  })

  test('dark mode matches baseline', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.emulateMedia({ colorScheme: 'dark' })
    await page.goto('/dashboard')
    expect(await page.screenshot()).toMatchSnapshot('dashboard-dark.png')
  })
})
```

**Best Practices:**
- ✅ Update baselines intentionally (after code review)
- ✅ Test multiple screen sizes (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- ✅ Test light and dark modes
- ✅ Test across browsers if styling differs
- ❌ Don't commit baseline changes without review
- ❌ Don't update baselines automatically

