## 13. CI/CD TEST GATES

### Standard: Progressive testing gates from pre-commit to production

**Pre-commit Hook (Developer):**
```bash
npm run lint      # 0 warnings
npm run type-check # 0 errors
npm run test      # All unit tests pass
```

**Pull Request (CI/CD):**
```bash
npm run lint              # Code quality
npm run type-check       # Type safety
npm run test             # Unit tests
npm run test:integration # API + DB tests
npm run test:e2e         # Critical paths (subset)
coverage check           # No decrease
npm audit               # No vulnerabilities
```

**Pre-Release (Staging):**
```bash
npm run test:e2e         # Full E2E suite
npm run test:a11y        # Full accessibility
npm run test:visual      # Visual regression
npm run test:performance # Load testing
Manual QA sign-off       # Checklist completion
```

**Production Release:**
```bash
Canary deployment        # 1% traffic
Monitor for 24 hours     # No errors/crashes
Gradual rollout          # 25% → 50% → 100%
Smoke tests on live      # Basic functionality
Incident response ready  # On-call team ready
```

