## 16. ANTI-PATTERNS TO AVOID

- ❌ Testing implementation details (test behavior)
- ❌ Too many assertions per test (one per test)
- ❌ Hardcoded test data (use fixtures)
- ❌ Shared state between tests (isolate each test)
- ❌ Sleeping in tests (use waitFor/expect)
- ❌ Skipped tests without issues (track and fix)
- ❌ 100% coverage target (realistic 80-90%)
- ❌ Testing third-party libraries (assume they work)
- ❌ No test data cleanup (causes cascading failures)
- ❌ Tests that depend on execution order (random order)

